<problem display_name="Linear Transformation" linenum="410" tex_filename="./hw/hw1.tex" showanswer="finished" attempts="4" rerandomize="per_student">
  <text>
    <center>
      <img src="/static/images/h1lintrans.svg" width="450 px" style="margin: 10px 25px 25px 25px; border:0px"/>
    </center>
    <p>
The vectors [mathjaxinline]u,v,w \in \mathbb R^2[/mathjaxinline] are given in the picture above. Recall that [mathjaxinline]\mathbb {P}[/mathjaxinline] is the space of all polynomials. Suppose that [mathjaxinline]T: \mathbb R^2 \rightarrow \mathbb {P}[/mathjaxinline] is a linear transformation, and that [mathjaxinline]T(u) = t^2 - 1[/mathjaxinline] and [mathjaxinline]T(v) = -2t + 3[/mathjaxinline]. What is [mathjaxinline]T(w)[/mathjaxinline]? </p>
    <p>
      <formularesponse type="cs" samples="t@1:5#10" answer="-t^2 -4*t + 7">
        <formulaequationinput size="50">
          <responseparam type="tolerance" default=".01"/>
        </formulaequationinput>
      </formularesponse>
    </p>
    <p>
      <solution>
        <font color="blue">Answer: </font>
        <font color="blue">
          <p>
Note from the picture that [mathjaxinline]w = -u + 2v.[/mathjaxinline] Hence </p>
          <table id="a0000000108" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]\begin{array}{rcl} T(w) &amp;  = &amp;  T(-u+2v) \\ &amp;  = &amp;  T(-u) + T(2v) \\ &amp;  = &amp;  -T(u) + 2T(v) \\ &amp;  = &amp;  -t^2 -4t + 7. \end{array}[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </font>
      </solution>
    </p>
  </text>
</problem>
